Subject: [PATCH] lv2/sysfs.h: pull <sys/param.h>; librt/fstat.c: write through timespec

sysFSStat and the reference CellFsStat both carry st_atime/st_mtime/st_ctime
members typed as time_t.  Newlib 4.4's <sys/stat.h> is POSIX-2008:
for non-SVR4 targets it declares timespec members st_atim/st_mtim/
st_ctim and then unconditionally #defines st_atime -> st_atim.tv_sec
etc.  Those macros bleed into every subsequent struct declaration
that happens to reuse the same member names.

Patch 0010 installs a PSL1GHT-owned <sys/stat.h> shadow that pulls
newlib's declarations via #include_next and then #undefines the
three legacy macros.  That's the load-bearing fix; the two changes
in this patch are the residual plumbing:

  * sysfs.h pulls <sys/param.h> so MAXPATHLEN is visible at the
    sysFSDirent typedef's declaration site (newlib 4.4 stopped
    transitively exposing it via <unistd.h> / <time.h>).

  * librt/fstat.c converts sysFSStat's time_t fields into newlib's
    timespec members via `dst->st_atim.tv_sec = src->st_atime`.
    Needs to be an explicit tv_sec write because newlib's struct
    stat holds timespec members, not bare time_t.  A TU-local
    #undef of the three macros keeps the assignment robust even in
    build configurations where the PSL1GHT shadow hasn't landed yet.

The previous version of this patch additionally added a
#pragma push_macro / #undef / pop_macro block around the sysFSStat
typedef in sysfs.h.  That was made redundant by 0010 and has been
removed.

diff --git a/ppu/include/lv2/sysfs.h b/ppu/include/lv2/sysfs.h
index 9bf0035..b43f2d5 100644
--- a/ppu/include/lv2/sysfs.h
+++ b/ppu/include/lv2/sysfs.h
@@ -3,6 +3,7 @@
 
 #include <time.h>
 #include <unistd.h>
+#include <sys/param.h>
 #include <ppu-types.h>
 
 // Open Flags
diff --git a/ppu/librt/fstat.c b/ppu/librt/fstat.c
index e59f50a..c35d85c 100644
--- a/ppu/librt/fstat.c
+++ b/ppu/librt/fstat.c
@@ -9,15 +9,24 @@
 
 #include <sys/file.h>
 
+/* Disable newlib's st_*time -> st_*tim.tv_sec rewrite inside this TU so
+ * that `src->st_atime` reads sysFSStat's literal field.  The dst side
+ * (newlib's struct stat) has literal st_atim/st_mtim/st_ctim timespec
+ * members; we write through tv_sec explicitly to avoid relying on the
+ * macro we just removed. */
+#undef st_atime
+#undef st_mtime
+#undef st_ctime
+
 static void convertLv2Stat(struct stat *dst,sysFSStat *src)
 {
 	memset(dst,0,sizeof(struct stat));
 	dst->st_mode = src->st_mode;
 	dst->st_uid = src->st_uid;
 	dst->st_gid = src->st_gid;
-	dst->st_atime = src->st_atime;
-	dst->st_mtime = src->st_mtime;
-	dst->st_ctime = src->st_ctime;
+	dst->st_atim.tv_sec = src->st_atime;
+	dst->st_mtim.tv_sec = src->st_mtime;
+	dst->st_ctim.tv_sec = src->st_ctime;
 	dst->st_size = src->st_size;
 	dst->st_blksize = src->st_blksize;
 
